The paper deals with object localization, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves using self-produced guidance masks to provide spatial correlation information to classification networks, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves extensive experiments and evaluation of the proposed method, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) categories.
